= Formation of a New Government

Following his election, [+ minister_president +] has worked to prepare a list of ministers for his cabinet that will be able to survive any motions of no confidence thrown its way. Now, it seems, he will present this list and confirm his appointments.

@aspelund
on-arrival: social_republican_r = sapt_r+lapt_r+rpt_r; grand_popular_front_r = kpt_r+sapt_r+lapt_r+rpt_r+avpt_r; popular_front_r = kpt_r+sapt_r+lapt_r+rpt_r; tower_r = sapt_r+lapt_r+rpt_r+avpt_r; economic_r = sapt_r+lapt_r+avpt_r+kpt_r; extended_tower_r = tower_r+tndp_r; extended_economic_r = economic_r+tndp_r
go-to: coalition_menu

With Aspelund once again serving at the helm, the presumptive coalition is a <span style="color: #d4130c;">Social</span><span style="color: #e49c21;">-</span><span style="color: #f5e324;">Republican</span> one. However, with the <span style="color: #f5e324;">**RPT**</span> doubling down on classical liberal economics and the expansion of the Aspelund coalition's size, it may be difficult to translate his victory into a stable government.

@coalition_menu

- @social_republican: We can form a <span style="color: #d4130c;">Social</span><span style="color: #e49c21;">-</span><span style="color: #f5e324;">Republican</span> government.
- @popular_front: We could form a new "Popular Front" coalition?
- @tower: The moderate parties can defend the tower together.
- @economic: An interventionist government must form to end the economic crisis.
- @failure: No government can be formed.

@social_republican
subtitle: <span style="color: #d4130c;">**SAPT**</span> + <span style="color: #e49c21;">**LAPT**</span> + <span style="color: #f5e324;">**RPT**</span> ([+ social_republican_r +]%)
choose-if: social_republican_r >= 50
on-arrival: rpt_willingness = rpt_relation; rpt_willingness += reformist_strength; rpt_willingness -= left_strength; rpt_willingness += pro_republic/2; rpt_willingness -= nationalism/2; rpt_willingness -= socialism/2

Thankfully, the simple option of another <span style="color: #d4130c;">Social</span><span style="color: #e49c21;">-</span><span style="color: #f5e324;">Republican</span> government remains open, and we will not need to do much negotiating beyond that. However, simple does not mean easy, and we will still have to find a better way to reconcile the major differences between our parties that led to the previous government's collapse.

- @rpt_agree: The <span style="color: #f5e324;">**RPT**</span> concedes.
- @rpt_bribe: We will work hard to convince the <span style="color: #f5e324;">**RPT**</span>.
- @rpt_refuse: The <span style="color: #f5e324;">**RPT**</span> refuses.

@popular_front
subtitle: <span style="color: #990000;">**KPT**</span> + <span style="color: #d4130c;">**SAPT**</span> + <span style="color: #e49c21;">**LAPT**</span> + <span style="color: #f5e324;">**RPT**</span>[? if not dahlin_avpt_backing : + <span style="color: #4e9933;">**AVPT**</span> ?]
