This is an unorthodox idea, to say the least. The <span style="color: #990000;">communists</span> and <span style="color: #f5e324;">republicans</span> on the surface seem to both loathe the idea. Can these differences be reconciled? [? if not dahlin_avpt_backing : There is also the <span style="color: #4e9933;">**AVPT**</span>, which could factor in and may have to depending on the willingness of liberal deputies to collaborate with communists. ?]

@tower
subtitle: <span style="color: #d4130c;">**SAPT**</span> + <span style="color: #e49c21;">**LAPT**</span> + <span style="color: #f5e324;">**RPT**</span> + <span style="color: #4e9933;">**AVPT**</span>[? if tower_r < 50 and extended_tower_r >= 50 : - perhaps the <span style="color: #a86b15;">**TNDP**</span> could complete this government? ?]
