A grouping together of those parties seeking to have the government direct economic resources in order to end the crisis - along economic lines, rather than ideological, bypassing the <span style="color: #f5e324;">republicans</span> - could be what the country needs in the long run to cement the Third Republic. [? if economic_r < 50 : This bloc does not itself have a majority, but if extended to include the opportunistic <span style="color: #a86b15;">**TNDP**</span>, it would. ?]

@failure
subtitle: Aspelund will be forced to form a government without the consent of his backers.

We have failed to form a government. What Aspelund will do now is uncertain - he could cave in and allow anti-republicans into government, resign, or something else. It's impossible to know. All that can be said is that he seems very frustrated with us, as well as the other parties backing him, for our inability to cooperate in defense of the republic.